item.title: CVE-2023-6142|2023-11-20T23:24:48.652Z -- dev%20blog -- dev%20blog
item.description: Dev blog v1.0 allows to exploit an XSS through an unrestricted file upload, together with a bad entropy of filenames. With this an attacker can upload a malicious HTML file, then guess the filename of the uploaded file and send it to a potential victim.
